article.headline: Emmett leads five Tech players in double figures
article.linkText: Texas Tech returns Knight to postseason winning form
article.story: RENO, Nev. (AP) -- True freshman Nick Fazekas recorded a double-double off the bench to lead Nevada to a 65-46 exhibition game win over Albertson College of Idaho Wednesday. Fazekas had a game-high 18 points and 14 rebounds for the Wolf Pack in its first exhibition game of the year. Marcelus Kemp hit three 3-pointers to score 16 points for Nevada, the preseason favorite in the Western Athletic Conference. The Pack led 20-18 before embarking on a 18-5 run over the final five minutes of the first half and the first three minutes of the second half to take control of the game. The Wolf Pack's biggest lead of the game was 20 late in the second half. Albertson was led by Andy Harper's 13 points. E.J. Costello and Reno native Steve Humphreys added 12 points for the Coyotes.
